oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Confederate soldiers buried in the "new" and "old" cemeteries at Fayetteville
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: List of Confederate Soldiers buried in the "New" and "Old" Cemeteries at Fayetteville. The document was found in the Little-McKinney-Young House attic in Fayetteville in 2002 among files belonging to Thomas Cheatham Little. The original is in the collections of the Lincoln County Archives.
